  "prompt": "Why should I not do a job in TCS?",
  "response": "Here are some potential drawbacks of working at TCS (Tata Consultancy Services):\n\n1. Work Culture Concerns\n- Can be bureaucratic\n- High employee turnover\n- Sometimes rigid management structure\n\n2. Work-Life Balance Issues\n- Long working hours\n- High stress levels\n- Frequent onsite/offshore job transfers\n- Potential for overtime without extra compensation\n\n3. Career Growth Limitations\n- Slower promotions\n- Limited skill diversity\n- Standardized career paths\n- Less personalized attention\n\n4. Compensation Challenges\n- Relatively lower salaries compared to other IT companies\n- Limited performance-based increments\n- Standard compensation packages\n\n5. Project Allocation\n- Less control over project selection\n- Potential for less interesting/challenging work\n- Assignments might not always match individual skills/interests\n\n6. Technical Learning\n- Sometimes repetitive work\n- Limited cutting-edge technology exposure\n- More focus on maintenance rather than innovation\n\n7. Client Interaction\n- Limited direct client engagement\n- More process-oriented approach\n- Less entrepreneurial environment\n\nThese are general observations, and individual experiences can vary. Some employees might find TCS a good fit depending on their career goals and expectations.\n\nConsider researching current employee reviews and speaking with current/former employees for more personalized insights.",
